{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Task-level review triage (round-4 verdicts: stories S2/S5/S6 + task S2b PASS+signed; 6 new tasks blocked). Fixed after fact-checking against repo config + the live instance docs:\n- S5b (biggest correction): the review was RIGHT — my All-Projects capability+submit design was wrong. project.config sets exclusiveGroupPermissions=submit (eclipses inherited All-Projects submit), and RebarBotNava is already in Contributors (holds Submit). And rebaseOnBehalfOfUploader is NOT a global [capability] — the Rebase access right is a per-ref ACL (confirmed in the instance access-control.html). Reworked S5b: drop the All-Projects script + submit grant; add the Rebase access right to the rebar project's refs/meta/config via setup-project.sh; verify Contributors membership. Fixed the S5 story pointer to match.\n- S2c: corrected ancestor-atomic submit to Gerrit 'Submitted Together' (relation-chain ancestry, reinforced by S3's assigned topic + active submitWholeTopic) AND added the review's valuable partial-land safety check (verify ALL members MERGED; loud error + hand-back otherwise).\n- S5c: fixed the alarm data-flow (CloudWatch alarms watch a published time_in_phase metric, not HTTP JSON) + added an AUTOLANDER_HANDBACK marker (lander_down is client-side) + concrete metric-shape proving test.\n- S5d: recovery rules now cover ALL four kill-point phases (rebasing/awaiting_verified → discard+re-select idempotently; submitting → Gerrit-check; handback → complete idempotent removal).\n- S2a: uploader/trailer-preservation test; S5a: autoheal-sidecar AC.\nRe-reviewing the 6 tasks + S5."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783832764637081001,"uuid":"535d7aa8-62cc-48ea-b659-afad33f56fc9"}